== Descendants == * {{ill|Kumano no Hirohama|ja|熊野広浜|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano no Hirohama|qq=}} served as a court official during the reigns of [[:en:Emperor Shōmu|Emperor Shōmu]] through {{ill|Empress Shōtoku|ja|称徳天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Empress Shōtoku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 孝謙天皇}}, achieving the Rank of Junior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade, before his death in 769 CE. * During the Heian period, the clan produced notable figures such as the head of the Masago clan, who was known as the "Elder of Masago." * The Kumano no Kuni no Miyatsuko lineage is also linked to the [[:en:Northern and Southern Courts period (disambiguation)|Nanbokuchō period]] and figures such as the {{ill|Wada clan (Kawachi)|ja|河内和田氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wada clan (Kawachi)|qq=}}, said to share descent with the {{ill|Kusunoki clan|ja|楠木氏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kusunoki clan|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite book|author=Ōta Ryō|title=Sei Shi Kakei Daijiten|year=1935|volume=2|pages=2144–2145|url=https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1130938/165}}</ref>
